30uint32 GetTargetFlagMask(SpellTargetObjectTypes objType)
31{
32 switch (objType)
33 {
34 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
35 return TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION;
36 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST:
37 return TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT;
38 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE_ALLY:
39 return TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ALLY;
40 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE_ENEMY:
41 return TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ENEMY;
42 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE:
43 return TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ALLY | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ENEMY;
44 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT:
45 return TARGET_FLAG_UNIT;
46 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ:
47 return TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT;
48 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ_ITEM:
49 return TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM;
50 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_ITEM:
51 return TARGET_FLAG_ITEM;
52 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_SRC:
53 return TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION;
54 default:
55 return TARGET_FLAG_NONE;
56 }
57}

64bool SpellImplicitTargetInfo::IsArea() const
65{
66 return GetSelectionCategory() == TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_AREA || GetSelectionCategory() == TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_CONE;
67}

94float SpellImplicitTargetInfo::CalcDirectionAngle() const
95{
96 switch (GetDirectionType())
97 {
98 case TARGET_DIR_FRONT:
99 return 0.0f;
100 case TARGET_DIR_BACK:
101 return static_cast<float>(M_PI);
102 case TARGET_DIR_RIGHT:
103 return static_cast<float>(-M_PI/2);
104 case TARGET_DIR_LEFT:
105 return static_cast<float>(M_PI/2);
106 case TARGET_DIR_FRONT_RIGHT:
107 return static_cast<float>(-M_PI/4);
108 case TARGET_DIR_BACK_RIGHT:
109 return static_cast<float>(-3*M_PI/4);
110 case TARGET_DIR_BACK_LEFT:
111 return static_cast<float>(3*M_PI/4);
112 case TARGET_DIR_FRONT_LEFT:
113 return static_cast<float>(M_PI/4);
114 case TARGET_DIR_RANDOM:
115 return float(rand_norm())*static_cast<float>(2*M_PI);
116 default:
117 return 0.0f;
118 }
119}

126uint32 SpellImplicitTargetInfo::GetExplicitTargetMask(bool& srcSet, bool& dstSet) const
127{
128 uint32 targetMask = 0;
129 if (GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_TRAJ)
130 {
131 if (!srcSet)
132 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION;
133 if (!dstSet)
134 targetMask |= TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION;
135 }
136 else
137 {
138 switch (GetReferenceType())
139 {
140 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_SRC:
141 if (srcSet)
142 break;
143 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION;
144 break;
145 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_DEST:
146 if (dstSet)
147 break;
148 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION;
149 break;
150 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_TARGET:
151 switch (GetObjectType())
152 {
153 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ:
154 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT;
155 break;
156 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ_ITEM:
157 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM;
158 break;
159 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST:
160 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT:
161 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
162 switch (GetCheckType())
163 {
164 case TARGET_CHECK_ENEMY:
165 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY;
166 break;
167 case TARGET_CHECK_ALLY:
168 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ALLY;
169 break;
170 case TARGET_CHECK_PARTY:
171 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PARTY;
172 break;
173 case TARGET_CHECK_RAID:
174 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_RAID;
175 break;
176 case TARGET_CHECK_PASSENGER:
177 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PASSENGER;
178 break;
179 case TARGET_CHECK_RAID_CLASS:
180 // nobreak;
181 default:
182 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT;
183 break;
184 }
185 break;
186 default:
187 break;
188 }
189 break;
190 default:
191 break;
192 }
193 }
194
195 switch (GetObjectType())
196 {
197 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_SRC:
198 srcSet = true;
199 break;
200 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
201 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST:
202 dstSet = true;
203 break;
204 default:
205 break;
206 }
207 return targetMask;
208}

362SpellEffectInfo::SpellEffectInfo(SpellEntry const* /*spellEntry*/, SpellInfo const* spellInfo, uint8 effIndex, SpellEffectEntry const* _effect)
363{
364 _spellInfo = spellInfo;
365 EffectIndex = _effect ? _effect->EffectIndex : effIndex;
366 Effect = _effect ? _effect->Effect : 0;
367 ApplyAuraName = _effect ? _effect->EffectAura : 0;
368 ApplyAuraPeriod = _effect ? _effect->EffectAuraPeriod : 0;
369 DieSides = _effect ? _effect->EffectDieSides : 0;
370 RealPointsPerLevel = _effect ? _effect->EffectRealPointsPerLevel : 0.0f;
371 BasePoints = _effect ? _effect->EffectBasePoints : 0;
372 PointsPerResource = _effect ? _effect->EffectPointsPerResource : 0.0f;
373 Amplitude = _effect ? _effect->EffectAmplitude : 0.0f;
374 ChainAmplitude = _effect ? _effect->EffectChainAmplitude : 0.0f;
375 BonusCoefficient = _effect ? _effect->EffectBonusCoefficient : 0.0f;
376 MiscValue = _effect ? _effect->EffectMiscValue : 0;
377 MiscValueB = _effect ? _effect->EffectMiscValueB : 0;
378 Mechanic = Mechanics(_effect ? _effect->EffectMechanic : 0);
379 PositionFacing = _effect ? _effect->EffectPosFacing : 0.0f;
380 TargetA = SpellImplicitTargetInfo(_effect ? _effect->ImplicitTarget[0] : 0);
381 TargetB = SpellImplicitTargetInfo(_effect ? _effect->ImplicitTarget[1] : 0);
382 RadiusEntry = _effect && _effect->EffectRadiusIndex ? sSpellRadiusStore.LookupEntry(_effect->EffectRadiusIndex) : NULL;
383 MaxRadiusEntry = _effect && _effect->EffectRadiusMaxIndex ? sSpellRadiusStore.LookupEntry(_effect->EffectRadiusMaxIndex) : NULL;
384 ChainTargets = _effect ? _effect->EffectChainTargets : 0;
385 ItemType = _effect ? _effect->EffectItemType : 0;
386 TriggerSpell = _effect ? _effect->EffectTriggerSpell : 0;
387 SpellClassMask = _effect ? _effect->EffectSpellClassMask : flag128();
388 BonusCoefficientFromAP = _effect ? _effect->BonusCoefficientFromAP : 0.0f;
389 ImplicitTargetConditions = NULL;
390
391 uint32 _effectScalingId = _effect ? sSpellEffectScallingByEffectId.find(_effect->ID) != sSpellEffectScallingByEffectId.end() ? sSpellEffectScallingByEffectId[_effect->ID] : 0 : 0;
392 SpellEffectScalingEntry const* _effectScalingEntry = sSpellEffectScalingStore.LookupEntry(_effectScalingId);
393
394 Scaling.Coefficient = _effectScalingEntry ? _effectScalingEntry->Coefficient : 0.0f;
395 Scaling.Variance = _effectScalingEntry ? _effectScalingEntry->Variance : 0.0f;
396 Scaling.ResourceCoefficient = _effectScalingEntry ? _effectScalingEntry->ResourceCoefficient : 0.0f;
397}

455int32 SpellEffectInfo::CalcValue(Unit const* caster /*= nullptr*/, int32 const* bp /*= nullptr*/, Unit const* target /*= nullptr*/, float* variance /*= nullptr*/, int32 itemLevel /*= -1*/) const
456{
457 float basePointsPerLevel = RealPointsPerLevel;
458 int32 basePoints = bp ? *bp : BasePoints;
459 float comboDamage = PointsPerResource;
460
461 // base amount modification based on spell lvl vs caster lvl
462 if (Scaling.Coefficient != 0.0f)
463 {
464 uint32 level = _spellInfo->SpellLevel;
465 if (target && _spellInfo->IsPositiveEffect(EffectIndex) && (Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA))
466 level = target->getLevel();
467 else if (caster)
468 level = caster->getLevel();
469
470 if (!_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR11_SCALES_WITH_ITEM_LEVEL) && _spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR10_UNK12))
471 level = _spellInfo->BaseLevel;
472
473 if (_spellInfo->Scaling.MaxScalingLevel && _spellInfo->Scaling.MaxScalingLevel > level)
474 level = _spellInfo->Scaling.MaxScalingLevel;
475
476 float value = 0.0f;
477 if (level > 0)
478 {
479 if (!_spellInfo->Scaling.Class)
480 return 0;
481
482 if (!_spellInfo->Scaling.ScalesFromItemLevel)
483 {
484 if (!_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR11_SCALES_WITH_ITEM_LEVEL))
485 {
486 if (GtSpellScalingEntry const* gtScaling = sGtSpellScalingStore.EvaluateTable(level - 1, (_spellInfo->Scaling.Class > 0 ? _spellInfo->Scaling.Class : ((MAX_CLASSES - 1 /*last class*/) - _spellInfo->Scaling.Class)) - 1))
487 value = gtScaling->value;
488 }
489 else
490 value = GetRandomPropertyPoints(itemLevel != -1 ? uint32(itemLevel) : 1u, ITEM_QUALITY_RARE, INVTYPE_CHEST, 0);
491 }
492 else
493 value = GetRandomPropertyPoints(_spellInfo->Scaling.ScalesFromItemLevel, ITEM_QUALITY_RARE, INVTYPE_CHEST, 0);
494
495 if (level < _spellInfo->Scaling.CastTimeMaxLevel && _spellInfo->Scaling.CastTimeMax)
496 value *= float(_spellInfo->Scaling.CastTimeMin + (level - 1) * (_spellInfo->Scaling.CastTimeMax - _spellInfo->Scaling.CastTimeMin) / (_spellInfo->Scaling.CastTimeMaxLevel - 1)) / float(_spellInfo->Scaling.CastTimeMax);
497
498 if (level < _spellInfo->Scaling.NerfMaxLevel)
499 value *= ((((1.0f - _spellInfo->Scaling.NerfFactor) * (level - 1)) / (_spellInfo->Scaling.NerfMaxLevel - 1)) + _spellInfo->Scaling.NerfFactor);
500 }
501
502 value *= Scaling.Coefficient;
503 if (value != 0.0f && value < 1.0f)
504 value = 1.0f;
505
506 if (Scaling.Variance)
507 {
508 float delta = fabs(Scaling.Variance * 0.5f);
509 float valueVariance = frand(-delta, delta);
510 value += value * valueVariance;
511
512 if (variance)
513 *variance = valueVariance;
514 }
515
516 basePoints = int32(value);
517
518 if (Scaling.ResourceCoefficient)
519 comboDamage = Scaling.ResourceCoefficient * value;
520 }
521 else
522 {
523 if (caster)
524 {
525 int32 level = int32(caster->getLevel());
526 if (level > int32(_spellInfo->MaxLevel) && _spellInfo->MaxLevel > 0)
527 level = int32(_spellInfo->MaxLevel);
528 else if (level < int32(_spellInfo->BaseLevel))
529 level = int32(_spellInfo->BaseLevel);
530 level -= int32(_spellInfo->SpellLevel);
531 basePoints += int32(level * basePointsPerLevel);
532 }
533
534 // roll in a range <1;EffectDieSides> as of patch 3.3.3
535 int32 randomPoints = int32(DieSides);
536 switch (randomPoints)
537 {
538 case 0: break;
539 case 1: basePoints += 1; break; // range 1..1
540 default:
541 {
542 // range can have positive (1..rand) and negative (rand..1) values, so order its for irand
543 int32 randvalue = (randomPoints >= 1)
544 ? irand(1, randomPoints)
545 : irand(randomPoints, 1);
546
547 basePoints += randvalue;
548 break;
549 }
550 }
551 }
552
553 float value = float(basePoints);
554
555 // random damage
556 if (caster)
557 {
558 // bonus amount from combo points
559 if (caster->m_movedPlayer && comboDamage)
560 if (uint8 comboPoints = caster->m_movedPlayer->GetComboPoints())
561 value += comboDamage * comboPoints;
562
563 value = caster->ApplyEffectModifiers(_spellInfo, EffectIndex, value);
564
565 // amount multiplication based on caster's level
566 if (!caster->IsControlledByPlayer() &&
567 _spellInfo->SpellLevel && _spellInfo->SpellLevel != caster->getLevel() &&
568 !basePointsPerLevel && (_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_LEVEL_DAMAGE_CALCULATION)))
569 {
570 bool canEffectScale = false;
571 switch (Effect)
572 {
573 case SPELL_EFFECT_SCHOOL_DAMAGE:
574 case SPELL_EFFECT_DUMMY:
575 case SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_DRAIN:
576 case SPELL_EFFECT_HEALTH_LEECH:
577 case SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL:
578 case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE:
579 case SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_BURN:
580 case SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT:
581 case SPELL_EFFECT_NORMALIZED_WEAPON_DMG:
582 case SPELL_EFFECT_FORCE_CAST_WITH_VALUE:
583 case SPELL_EFFECT_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
584 case SPELL_EFFECT_TRIGGER_MISSILE_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
585 canEffectScale = true;
586 break;
587 default:
588 break;
589 }
590
591 switch (ApplyAuraName)
592 {
593 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
594 case SPELL_AURA_DUMMY:
595 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL:
596 case SPELL_AURA_DAMAGE_SHIELD:
597 case SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_DAMAGE:
598 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
599 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_MANA_LEECH:
600 case SPELL_AURA_SCHOOL_ABSORB:
601 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
602 canEffectScale = true;
603 break;
604 default:
605 break;
606 }
607
608 if (canEffectScale)
609 {
610 GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* spellScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.EvaluateTable(_spellInfo->SpellLevel - 1, 0);
611 GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* casterScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.EvaluateTable(caster->getLevel() - 1, 0);
612 if (spellScaler && casterScaler)
613 value *= casterScaler->ratio / spellScaler->ratio;
614 }
615 }
616 }
617
618 return int32(value);
619}
620
621int32 SpellEffectInfo::CalcBaseValue(int32 value) const
622{
623 if (DieSides == 0)
624 return value;
625 else
626 return value - 1;

654
655float SpellEffectInfo::CalcRadius(Unit* caster, Spell* spell) const
656{
657 const SpellRadiusEntry* entry = RadiusEntry;
658 if (!HasRadius() && HasMaxRadius())
659 entry = MaxRadiusEntry;
660
661 if (!entry)
662 return 0.0f;
663
664 float radius = entry->RadiusMin;
665
666 // Client uses max if min is 0
667 if (radius == 0.0f)
668 radius = entry->RadiusMax;
669
670 if (caster)
671 {
672 radius += entry->RadiusPerLevel * caster->getLevel();
673 radius = std::min(radius, entry->RadiusMax);
674 if (Player* modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
675 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_RADIUS, radius, spell);
676 }
677
678 return radius;
679}

685
686uint32 SpellEffectInfo::GetMissingTargetMask(bool srcSet /*= false*/, bool dstSet /*= false*/, uint32 mask /*=0*/) const
687{
688 uint32 effImplicitTargetMask = GetTargetFlagMask(GetUsedTargetObjectType());
689 uint32 providedTargetMask = GetTargetFlagMask(TargetA.GetObjectType()) | GetTargetFlagMask(TargetB.GetObjectType()) | mask;
690
691 // remove all flags covered by effect target mask
692 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK)
693 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK);
694 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK)
695 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK);
696 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM)
697 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_ITEM);
698 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT)
699 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM);
700 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_ITEM)
701 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_ITEM | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM);
702 if (dstSet || providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
703 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION);
704 if (srcSet || providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION)
705 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION);
706
707 return effImplicitTargetMask;
708}

1156void SpellInfo::_UnloadSpellEffects()
1157{
1158 for (SpellEffectInfoMap::value_type& i : _effects)

1160 delete i.second[j];
1161 _effects.clear();
1162}

1235 || Id == 64323;

1243 (effect0->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_CREATE_ITEM_2 &&
1244 ((TotemCategory[0] != 0 || (Totem[0] != 0 && SpellIconID == 1)) || effect0->ItemType == 0)));

1307bool SpellInfo::IsAbilityLearnedWithProfession() const
1308{
1309 SkillLineAbilityMapBounds bounds = sSpellMgr->GetSkillLineAbilityMapBounds(Id);
1310
1311 for (SkillLineAbilityMap::const_iterator _spell_idx = bounds.first; _spell_idx != bounds.second; ++_spell_idx)
1312 {
1313 SkillLineAbilityEntry const* pAbility = _spell_idx->second;
1314 if (!pAbility || pAbility->AquireMethod != SKILL_LINE_ABILITY_LEARNED_ON_SKILL_VALUE)
1315 continue;
1316
1317 if (pAbility->MinSkillLineRank > 0)
1318 return true;
1319 }
1320
1321 return false;
1322}

1324bool SpellInfo::IsAbilityOfSkillType(uint32 skillType) const
1325{
1326 SkillLineAbilityMapBounds bounds = sSpellMgr->GetSkillLineAbilityMapBounds(Id);
1327
1328 for (SkillLineAbilityMap::const_iterator _spell_idx = bounds.first; _spell_idx != bounds.second; ++_spell_idx)
1329 if (_spell_idx->second->SkillLine == uint32(skillType))
1330 return true;
1331
1332 return false;
1333}

1363bool SpellInfo::NeedsToBeTriggeredByCaster(SpellInfo const* triggeringSpell, uint32 difficulty) const
1364{
1365 if (NeedsExplicitUnitTarget())
1366 return true;
1367
1368 /*
1369 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1370 {
1371 if (Effects[i].IsEffect())
1372 {
1373 if (Effects[i].TargetA.GetSelectionCategory() == TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_CHANNEL
1374 || Effects[i].TargetB.GetSelectionCategory() == TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_CHANNEL)
1375 return true;
1376 }
1377 }
1378 */
1379
1380 if (triggeringSpell->IsChanneled())
1381 {
1382 uint32 mask = 0;
1383 SpellEffectInfoVector effects = GetEffectsForDifficulty(difficulty);
1384 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : effects)
1385 {
1386 if (!effect)
1387 continue;
1388
1389 if (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_UNIT_CASTER && effect->TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_DEST_CASTER
1390 && effect->TargetB.GetTarget() != TARGET_UNIT_CASTER && effect->TargetB.GetTarget() != TARGET_DEST_CASTER)
1391 {
1392 mask |= effect->GetProvidedTargetMask();
1393 }
1394 }
1395
1396 if (mask & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK)
1397 return true;
1398 }
1399
1400 return false;
1401}

1426 return false;

1562bool SpellInfo::CanPierceImmuneAura(SpellInfo const* aura) const
1563{
1564 // these spells pierce all avalible spells (Resurrection Sickness for example)
1565 if (Attributes & SPELL_ATTR0_UNAFFECTED_BY_INVULNERABILITY)
1566 return true;
1567
1568 // these spells (Cyclone for example) can pierce all... // ...but not these (Divine shield, Ice block, Cyclone and Banish for example)
1569 if ((AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_UNAFFECTED_BY_SCHOOL_IMMUNE) && !(aura && (aura->Mechanic == MECHANIC_IMMUNE_SHIELD || aura->Mechanic == MECHANIC_INVULNERABILITY || aura->Mechanic == MECHANIC_BANISH)))
1570 return true;
1571
1572 return false;
1573}

1575bool SpellInfo::CanDispelAura(SpellInfo const* aura) const
1576{
1577 // These spells (like Mass Dispel) can dispell all auras, except death persistent ones (like Dungeon and Battleground Deserter)
1578 if (Attributes & SPELL_ATTR0_UNAFFECTED_BY_INVULNERABILITY && !aura->IsDeathPersistent())
1579 return true;
1580
1581 // These auras (like Divine Shield) can't be dispelled
1582 if (aura->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_UNAFFECTED_BY_INVULNERABILITY))
1583 return false;
1584
1585 // These auras (Cyclone for example) are not dispelable
1586 if (aura->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_UNAFFECTED_BY_SCHOOL_IMMUNE))
1587 return false;
1588
1589 return true;
1590}

1661SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckShapeshift(uint32 form) const
1662{
1663 // talents that learn spells can have stance requirements that need ignore
1664 // (this requirement only for client-side stance show in talent description)
1665 /* TODO: 6.x fix this in proper way (probably spell flags/attributes?)
1666 if (GetTalentSpellCost(Id) > 0 &&
1667 (Effects[0].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL || Effects[1].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL || Effects[2].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL))
1668 return SPELL_CAST_OK;*/
1669
1670 //if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR13_ACTIVATES_REQUIRED_SHAPESHIFT))
1671 // return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1672
1673 uint64 stanceMask = (form ? UI64LIT(1) << (form - 1) : 0);
1674
1675 if (stanceMask & StancesNot) // can explicitly not be cast in this stance
1676 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_SHAPESHIFT;
1677
1678 if (stanceMask & Stances) // can explicitly be cast in this stance
1679 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1680
1681 bool actAsShifted = false;
1682 SpellShapeshiftFormEntry const* shapeInfo = NULL;
1683 if (form > 0)
1684 {
1685 shapeInfo = sSpellShapeshiftFormStore.LookupEntry(form);
1686 if (!shapeInfo)
1687 {
1688 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "GetErrorAtShapeshiftedCast: unknown shapeshift %u", form);
1689 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1690 }
1691 actAsShifted = !(shapeInfo->Flags & 1); // shapeshift acts as normal form for spells
1692 }
1693
1694 if (actAsShifted)
1695 {
1696 if (Attributes & SPELL_ATTR0_NOT_SHAPESHIFT) // not while shapeshifted
1697 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_SHAPESHIFT;
1698 else if (Stances != 0) // needs other shapeshift
1699 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_SHAPESHIFT;
1700 }
1701 else
1702 {
1703 // needs shapeshift
1704 if (!(AttributesEx2 & SPELL_ATTR2_NOT_NEED_SHAPESHIFT) && Stances != 0)
1705 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_SHAPESHIFT;
1706 }
1707
1708 // Check if stance disables cast of not-stance spells
1709 // Example: cannot cast any other spells in zombie or ghoul form
1710 /// @todo Find a way to disable use of these spells clientside
1711 if (shapeInfo && shapeInfo->Flags & 0x400)
1712 {
1713 if (!(stanceMask & Stances))
1714 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_SHAPESHIFT;
1715 }
1716
1717 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1718}
1719
1720SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckLocation(uint32 map_id, uint32 zone_id, uint32 area_id, Player const* player) const
1721{
1722 // normal case
1723 if (RequiredAreasID > 0)
1724 {
1725 bool found = false;
1726 std::vector<uint32> areaGroupMembers = sDB2Manager.GetAreasForGroup(RequiredAreasID);
1727 for (uint32 areaId : areaGroupMembers)
1728 {
1729 if (areaId == zone_id || areaId == area_id)
1730 {
1731 found = true;
1732 break;
1733 }
1734 }
1735
1736 if (!found)
1737 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1738 }
1739
1740 // continent limitation (virtual continent)
1741 if (AttributesEx4 & SPELL_ATTR4_CAST_ONLY_IN_OUTLAND)
1742 {
1743 uint32 v_map = GetVirtualMapForMapAndZone(map_id, zone_id);
1744 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(v_map);
1745 if (!mapEntry || mapEntry->ExpansionID < 1 || !mapEntry->IsContinent())
1746 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1747 }
1748
1749 // raid instance limitation
1750 if (AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_NOT_IN_RAID_INSTANCE)
1751 {
1752 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1753 if (!mapEntry || mapEntry->IsRaid())
1754 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_IN_RAID_INSTANCE;
1755 }
1756
1757 // DB base check (if non empty then must fit at least single for allow)
1758 SpellAreaMapBounds saBounds = sSpellMgr->GetSpellAreaMapBounds(Id);
1759 if (saBounds.first != saBounds.second)
1760 {
1761 for (SpellAreaMap::const_iterator itr = saBounds.first; itr != saBounds.second; ++itr)
1762 {
1763 if (itr->second.IsFitToRequirements(player, zone_id, area_id))
1764 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1765 }
1766 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1767 }
1768
1769 // bg spell checks
1770 switch (Id)
1771 {
1772 case 23333: // Warsong Flag
1773 case 23335: // Silverwing Flag
1774 return map_id == 489 && player && player->InBattleground() ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1775 case 34976: // Netherstorm Flag
1776 return map_id == 566 && player && player->InBattleground() ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1777 case 2584: // Waiting to Resurrect
1778 case 22011: // Spirit Heal Channel
1779 case 22012: // Spirit Heal
1780 case 24171: // Resurrection Impact Visual
1781 case 42792: // Recently Dropped Flag
1782 case 43681: // Inactive
1783 case 44535: // Spirit Heal (mana)
1784 {
1785 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1786 if (!mapEntry)
1787 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1788
1789 return zone_id == 4197 || (mapEntry->IsBattleground() && player && player->InBattleground()) ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1790 }
1791 case 44521: // Preparation
1792 {
1793 if (!player)
1794 return SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1795
1796 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1797 if (!mapEntry)
1798 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1799
1800 if (!mapEntry->IsBattleground())
1801 return SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1802
1803 Battleground* bg = player->GetBattleground();
1804 return bg && bg->GetStatus() == STATUS_WAIT_JOIN ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1805 }
1806 case 32724: // Gold Team (Alliance)
1807 case 32725: // Green Team (Alliance)
1808 case 35774: // Gold Team (Horde)
1809 case 35775: // Green Team (Horde)
1810 {
1811 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1812 if (!mapEntry)
1813 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1814
1815 return mapEntry->IsBattleArena() && player && player->InBattleground() ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1816 }
1817 case 32727: // Arena Preparation
1818 {
1819 if (!player)
1820 return SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1821
1822 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1823 if (!mapEntry)
1824 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1825
1826 if (!mapEntry->IsBattleArena())
1827 return SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1828
1829 Battleground* bg = player->GetBattleground();
1830 return bg && bg->GetStatus() == STATUS_WAIT_JOIN ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1831 }
1832 }
1833
1834 // aura limitations
1835 if (player)
1836 {
1837 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffectsForDifficulty(player->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID()))
1838 {
1839 if (!effect || !effect->IsAura())
1840 continue;
1841
1842 switch (effect->ApplyAuraName)
1843 {
1844 case SPELL_AURA_FLY:
1845 {
1846 SkillLineAbilityMapBounds bounds = sSpellMgr->GetSkillLineAbilityMapBounds(Id);
1847 for (SkillLineAbilityMap::const_iterator skillIter = bounds.first; skillIter != bounds.second; ++skillIter)
1848 {
1849 if (skillIter->second->SkillLine == SKILL_MOUNTS)
1850 if (!player->CanFlyInZone(map_id, zone_id))
1851 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1852 }
1853 break;
1854 }
1855 case SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED:
1856 {
1857 uint32 mountType = effect->MiscValueB;
1858 if (MountEntry const* mountEntry = sDB2Manager.GetMount(Id))
1859 mountType = mountEntry->MountTypeId;
1860 if (mountType && !player->GetMountCapability(mountType))
1861 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_HERE;
1862 break;
1863 }
1864 }
1865 }
1866 }
1867
1868 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1869}
1870
1871SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckTarget(Unit const* caster, WorldObject const* target, bool implicit) const
1872{
1873 if (AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_CANT_TARGET_SELF && caster == target)
1874 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1875
1876 // check visibility - ignore stealth for implicit (area) targets
1877 if (!(AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_CAN_TARGET_INVISIBLE) && !caster->CanSeeOrDetect(target, implicit))
1878 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1879
1880 Unit const* unitTarget = target->ToUnit();
1881
1882 // creature/player specific target checks
1883 if (unitTarget)
1884 {
1885 if (AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_CANT_TARGET_IN_COMBAT)
1886 {
1887 if (unitTarget->IsInCombat())
1888 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AFFECTING_COMBAT;
1889 // player with active pet counts as a player in combat
1890 else if (Player const* player = unitTarget->ToPlayer())
1891 if (Pet* pet = player->GetPet())
1892 if (pet->GetVictim() && !pet->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_CONTROLLED))
1893 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AFFECTING_COMBAT;
1894 }
1895
1896 // only spells with SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_TARGET_GHOSTS can target ghosts
1897 if (((AttributesEx3 & SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_TARGET_GHOSTS) != 0) != unitTarget->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_GHOST))
1898 {
1899 if (AttributesEx3 & SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_TARGET_GHOSTS)
1900 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NOT_GHOST;
1901 else
1902 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1903 }
1904
1905 if (caster != unitTarget)
1906 {
1907 if (caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1908 {
1909 // Do not allow these spells to target creatures not tapped by us (Banish, Polymorph, many quest spells)
1910 if (AttributesEx2 & SPELL_ATTR2_CANT_TARGET_TAPPED)
1911 if (Creature const* targetCreature = unitTarget->ToCreature())
1912 if (targetCreature->hasLootRecipient() && !targetCreature->isTappedBy(caster->ToPlayer()))
1913 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_CAST_ON_TAPPED;
1914
1915 if (AttributesCu & SPELL_ATTR0_CU_PICKPOCKET)
1916 {
1917 if (unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1918 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1919 else if ((unitTarget->GetCreatureTypeMask() & CREATURE_TYPEMASK_HUMANOID_OR_UNDEAD) == 0)
1920 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NO_POCKETS;
1921 }
1922
1923 // Not allow disarm unarmed player
1924 if (Mechanic == MECHANIC_DISARM)
1925 {
1926 if (unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1927 {
1928 Player const* player = unitTarget->ToPlayer();
1929 if (!player->GetWeaponForAttack(BASE_ATTACK) || !player->IsUseEquipedWeapon(true))
1930 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NO_WEAPONS;
1931 }
1932 else if (!unitTarget->GetVirtualItemId(0))
1933 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NO_WEAPONS;
1934 }
1935 }
1936 }
1937 }
1938 // corpse specific target checks
1939 else if (Corpse const* corpseTarget = target->ToCorpse())
1940 {
1941 // cannot target bare bones
1942 if (corpseTarget->GetType() == CORPSE_BONES)
1943 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1944 // we have to use owner for some checks (aura preventing resurrection for example)
1945 if (Player* owner = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(corpseTarget->GetOwnerGUID()))
1946 unitTarget = owner;
1947 // we're not interested in corpses without owner
1948 else
1949 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1950 }
1951 // other types of objects - always valid
1952 else return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1953
1954 // corpseOwner and unit specific target checks
1955 if (AttributesEx3 & SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_TARGET_PLAYERS && !unitTarget->ToPlayer())
1956 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NOT_PLAYER;
1957
1958 if (!IsAllowingDeadTarget() && !unitTarget->IsAlive())
1959 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGETS_DEAD;
1960
1961 // check this flag only for implicit targets (chain and area), allow to explicitly target units for spells like Shield of Righteousness
1962 if (implicit && AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_CANT_TARGET_CROWD_CONTROLLED && !unitTarget->CanFreeMove())
1963 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1964
1965 // checked in Unit::IsValidAttack/AssistTarget, shouldn't be checked for ENTRY targets
1966 //if (!(AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_CAN_TARGET_UNTARGETABLE) && target->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_NOT_SELECTABLE))
1967 // return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1968
1969 //if (!(AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_CAN_TARGET_POSSESSED_FRIENDS)
1970
1971 if (!CheckTargetCreatureType(unitTarget))
1972 {
1973 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1974 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_IS_PLAYER;
1975 else
1976 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1977 }
1978
1979 // check GM mode and GM invisibility - only for player casts (npc casts are controlled by AI) and negative spells
1980 if (unitTarget != caster && (caster->IsControlledByPlayer() || !IsPositive()) && unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1981 {
1982 if (!unitTarget->ToPlayer()->IsVisible())
1983 return SPELL_FAILED_BM_OR_INVISGOD;
1984
1985 if (unitTarget->ToPlayer()->IsGameMaster())
1986 return SPELL_FAILED_BM_OR_INVISGOD;
1987 }
1988
1989 // not allow casting on flying player
1990 if (unitTarget->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_IN_FLIGHT) && !(AttributesCu & SPELL_ATTR0_CU_ALLOW_INFLIGHT_TARGET))
1991 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1992
1993 /* TARGET_UNIT_MASTER gets blocked here for passengers, because the whole idea of this check is to
1994 not allow passengers to be implicitly hit by spells, however this target type should be an exception,
1995 if this is left it kills spells that award kill credit from vehicle to master (few spells),
1996 the use of these 2 covers passenger target check, logically, if vehicle cast this to master it should always hit
1997 him, because it would be it's passenger, there's no such case where this gets to fail legitimacy, this problem
1998 cannot be solved from within the check in other way since target type cannot be called for the spell currently
1999 Spell examples: [ID - 52864 Devour Water, ID - 52862 Devour Wind, ID - 49370 Wyrmrest Defender: Destabilize Azure Dragonshrine Effect] */
2000 if (!caster->IsVehicle() && !(caster->GetCharmerOrOwner() == target))
2001 {
2002 if (TargetAuraState && !unitTarget->HasAuraState(AuraStateType(TargetAuraState), this, caster))
2003 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
2004
2005 if (ExcludeTargetAuraState && unitTarget->HasAuraState(AuraStateType(ExcludeTargetAuraState), this, caster))
2006 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
2007 }
2008
2009 if (TargetAuraSpell && !unitTarget->HasAura(TargetAuraSpell))
2010 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
2011
2012 if (ExcludeTargetAuraSpell && unitTarget->HasAura(ExcludeTargetAuraSpell))
2013 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
2014
2015 if (unitTarget->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_PREVENT_RESURRECTION))
2016 if (HasEffect(caster->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID(), SPELL_EFFECT_SELF_RESURRECT) || HasEffect(caster->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID(), SPELL_EFFECT_RESURRECT) || HasEffect(caster->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID(), SPELL_EFFECT_RESURRECT_NEW))
2017 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_CANNOT_BE_RESURRECTED;
2018
2019 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
2020}
2021
2022SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckExplicitTarget(Unit const* caster, WorldObject const* target, Item const* itemTarget) const
2023{
2024 uint32 neededTargets = GetExplicitTargetMask();
2025 if (!target)
2026 {
2027 if (neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK))
2028 if (!(neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM) || !itemTarget)
2029 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
2030 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
2031 }
2032
2033 if (Unit const* unitTarget = target->ToUnit())
2034 {
2035 if (neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ALLY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_RAID | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PARTY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MINIPET | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PASSENGER))
2036 {
2037 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY)
2038 if (caster->_IsValidAttackTarget(unitTarget, this))
2039 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
2040 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ALLY
2041 || (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PARTY && caster->IsInPartyWith(unitTarget))
2042 || (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_RAID && caster->IsInRaidWith(unitTarget)))
2043 if (caster->_IsValidAssistTarget(unitTarget, this))
2044 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
2045 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MINIPET)
2046 if (unitTarget->GetGUID() == caster->GetCritterGUID())
2047 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
2048 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PASSENGER)
2049 if (unitTarget->IsOnVehicle(caster))
2050 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
2051 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
2052 }
2053 }
2054 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
2055}
2056
2057SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckVehicle(Unit const* caster) const
2058{
2059 // All creatures should be able to cast as passengers freely, restriction and attribute are only for players
2060 if (caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
2061 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
2062
2063 Vehicle* vehicle = caster->GetVehicle();
2064 if (vehicle)
2065 {
2066 uint16 checkMask = 0;
2067 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffectsForDifficulty(caster->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID()))
2068 {
2069 if (effect && effect->ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT)
2070 {
2071 SpellShapeshiftFormEntry const* shapeShiftFromEntry = sSpellShapeshiftFormStore.LookupEntry(effect->MiscValue);
2072 if (shapeShiftFromEntry && (shapeShiftFromEntry->Flags & 1) == 0) // unk flag
2073 checkMask |= VEHICLE_SEAT_FLAG_UNCONTROLLED;
2074 break;
2075 }
2076 }
2077
2078 if (HasAura(caster->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID(), SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED))
2079 checkMask |= VEHICLE_SEAT_FLAG_CAN_CAST_MOUNT_SPELL;
2080
2081 if (!checkMask)
2082 checkMask = VEHICLE_SEAT_FLAG_CAN_ATTACK;
2083
2084 VehicleSeatEntry const* vehicleSeat = vehicle->GetSeatForPassenger(caster);
2085 if (!(AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_CASTABLE_WHILE_ON_VEHICLE) && !(Attributes & SPELL_ATTR0_CASTABLE_WHILE_MOUNTED)
2086 && (vehicleSeat->Flags & checkMask) != checkMask)
2087 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_DO_THAT_RIGHT_NOW;
2088
2089 // Can only summon uncontrolled minions/guardians when on controlled vehicle
2090 if (vehicleSeat->Flags & (VEHICLE_SEAT_FLAG_CAN_CONTROL | VEHICLE_SEAT_FLAG_UNK2))
2091 {
2092 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffectsForDifficulty(caster->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID()))
2093 {
2094 if (!effect || effect->Effect != SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON)
2095 continue;
2096
2097 SummonPropertiesEntry const* props = sSummonPropertiesStore.LookupEntry(effect->MiscValueB);
2098 if (props && props->Category != SUMMON_CATEGORY_WILD)
2099 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_DO_THAT_RIGHT_NOW;
2100 }
2101 }
2102 }
2103
2104 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
2105}

2217AuraStateType SpellInfo::GetAuraState(uint32 difficulty) const
2218{
2219 // Seals
2220 if (GetSpellSpecific() == SPELL_SPECIFIC_SEAL)
2221 return AURA_STATE_JUDGEMENT;
2222
2223 // Conflagrate aura state on Immolate and Shadowflame
2224 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK &&
2225 // Immolate
2226 ((SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 4) ||
2227 // Shadowflame
2228 (SpellFamilyFlags[2] & 2)))
2229 return AURA_STATE_CONFLAGRATE;
2230
2231 // Faerie Fire (druid versions)
2232 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_DRUID && SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x400)
2233 return AURA_STATE_FAERIE_FIRE;
2234
2235 // Sting (hunter's pet ability)
2236 if (GetCategory() == 1133)
2237 return AURA_STATE_FAERIE_FIRE;
2238
2239 // Victorious
2240 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARRIOR && SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x00040000)
2241 return AURA_STATE_WARRIOR_VICTORY_RUSH;
2242
2243 // Swiftmend state on Regrowth & Rejuvenation
2244 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_DRUID && SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x50)
2245 return AURA_STATE_SWIFTMEND;
2246
2247 // Deadly poison aura state
2248 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE && SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x10000)
2249 return AURA_STATE_DEADLY_POISON;
2250
2251 // Enrage aura state
2252 if (Dispel == DISPEL_ENRAGE)
2253 return AURA_STATE_ENRAGE;
2254
2255 // Bleeding aura state
2256 if (GetAllEffectsMechanicMask() & 1<<MECHANIC_BLEED)
2257 return AURA_STATE_BLEEDING;
2258
2259 if (GetSchoolMask() & SPELL_SCHOOL_MASK_FROST)
2260 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffectsForDifficulty(difficulty))
2261 if (effect && effect->IsAura() && (effect->ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_STUN
2262 || effect->ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_ROOT))
2263 return AURA_STATE_FROZEN;
2264
2265 switch (Id)
2266 {
2267 case 71465: // Divine Surge
2268 case 50241: // Evasive Charges
2269 return AURA_STATE_UNKNOWN22;
2270 default:
2271 break;
2272 }
2273
2274 return AURA_STATE_NONE;
2275}

2277SpellSpecificType SpellInfo::GetSpellSpecific() const
2278{
2279 switch (SpellFamilyName)
2280 {
2281 case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
2282 {
2283 // Food / Drinks (mostly)
2284 if (AuraInterruptFlags & AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_NOT_SEATED)
2285 {
2286 bool food = false;
2287 bool drink = false;
2288 for (SpellEffectInfoMap::const_iterator itr = _effects.begin(); itr != _effects.end(); ++itr)
2289 {
2290 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : itr->second)
2291 {
2292 if (!effect || !effect->IsAura())
2293 continue;
2294 switch (effect->ApplyAuraName)
2295 {
2296 // Food
2297 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_REGEN:
2298 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_HEALTH:
2299 food = true;
2300 break;
2301 // Drink
2302 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_REGEN:
2303 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_POWER:
2304 drink = true;
2305 break;
2306 default:
2307 break;
2308 }
2309 }
2310 }
2311
2312 if (food && drink)
2313 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_FOOD_AND_DRINK;
2314 else if (food)
2315 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_FOOD;
2316 else if (drink)
2317 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_DRINK;
2318 }
2319 // scrolls effects
2320 else
2321 {
2322 SpellInfo const* firstRankSpellInfo = GetFirstRankSpell();
2323 switch (firstRankSpellInfo->Id)
2324 {
2325 case 8118: // Strength
2326 case 8099: // Stamina
2327 case 8112: // Spirit
2328 case 8096: // Intellect
2329 case 8115: // Agility
2330 case 8091: // Armor

2334 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_WARRIOR_ENRAGE;
2335 }
2336 }
2337 break;
2338 }
2339 case SPELLFAMILY_MAGE:
2340 {
2341 // family flags 18(Molten), 25(Frost/Ice), 28(Mage)
2342 if (SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x12040000)
2343 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_MAGE_ARMOR;
2344
2345 // Arcane brillance and Arcane intelect (normal check fails because of flags difference)
2346 if (SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x400)
2347 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_MAGE_ARCANE_BRILLANCE;
2348 SpellEffectInfo const* effect = GetEffect(DIFFICULTY_NONE, EFFECT_0);
2349 if (effect && (SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x1000000) && effect->ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_CONFUSE)
2350 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_MAGE_POLYMORPH;
2351
2352 break;
2353 }
2354 case SPELLFAMILY_WARRIOR:
2355 {
2356 if (Id == 12292) // Death Wish
2357 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_WARRIOR_ENRAGE;
2358
2359 break;
2360 }
2361 case SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK:
2362 {
2363 // Warlock (Bane of Doom | Bane of Agony | Bane of Havoc)
2364 if (Id == 603 || Id == 980 || Id == 80240)
2365 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_BANE;
2366
2367 // only warlock curses have this
2368 if (Dispel == DISPEL_CURSE)
2369 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_CURSE;
2370
2371 // Warlock (Demon Armor | Demon Skin | Fel Armor)
2372 if (SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x20000020 || SpellFamilyFlags[2] & 0x00000010)
2373 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_WARLOCK_ARMOR;
2374
2375 //seed of corruption and corruption
2376 if (SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x10 || SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x2)
2377 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_WARLOCK_CORRUPTION;
2378 break;
2379 }
2380 case SPELLFAMILY_PRIEST:
2381 {
2382 // Divine Spirit and Prayer of Spirit

2384 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_PRIEST_DIVINE_SPIRIT;
2385
2386 break;
2387 }
2388 case SPELLFAMILY_HUNTER:
2389 {
2390 // only hunter stings have this
2391 if (Dispel == DISPEL_POISON)
2392 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_STING;
2393
2394 // only hunter aspects have this (but not all aspects in hunter family)
2395 if (SpellFamilyFlags & flag128(0x00200000, 0x00000000, 0x00001010, 0x00000000))
2396 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_ASPECT;
2397
2398 break;
2399 }
2400 case SPELLFAMILY_PALADIN:
2401 {
2402 // Collection of all the seal family flags. No other paladin spell has any of those.
2403 if (SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0xA2000800)
2404 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_SEAL;
2405
2406 if (SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x00002190)
2407 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_HAND;
2408
2409 // Judgement
2410 if (Id == 20271)
2411 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_JUDGEMENT;
2412
2413 // only paladin auras have this (for palaldin class family)

2415 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_AURA;

2417 break;

2419 case SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN:
2420 {

2423 || SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x00000400
2424 || Id == 23552)

2426

2431 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_PRESENCE;

2433 }
2434
2435 for (SpellEffectInfoMap::const_iterator itr = _effects.begin(); itr != _effects.end(); ++itr)
2436 {
2437 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : itr->second)
2438 {
2439 if (effect && effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
2440 {
2441 switch (effect->ApplyAuraName)

2447 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_CHARM;

2452 case SPELL_AURA_TRACK_RESOURCES:
2453 case SPELL_AURA_TRACK_STEALTHED:
2454 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_TRACKER;
2455 }
2456 }
2457 }
2458 }
2459 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_NORMAL;
2460}

2500uint32 SpellInfo::CalcCastTime(uint8 level, Spell* spell /*= NULL*/) const
2501{
2502 int32 castTime = 0;
2503 if (!level && spell)
2504 level = spell->GetCaster()->getLevel();
2505
2506 // not all spells have cast time index and this is all is pasiive abilities
2507 if (level && Scaling.CastTimeMax > 0)
2508 {
2509 castTime = Scaling.CastTimeMax;
2510 if (Scaling.CastTimeMaxLevel > level)
2511 castTime = Scaling.CastTimeMin + int32(level - 1) * (Scaling.CastTimeMax - Scaling.CastTimeMin) / (Scaling.CastTimeMaxLevel - 1);
2512 }
2513 else if (CastTimeEntry)
2514 castTime = CastTimeEntry->CastTime;
2515
2516 if (!castTime)
2517 return 0;
2518
2519 if (spell)
2520 spell->GetCaster()->ModSpellCastTime(this, castTime, spell);
2521
2522 if (Attributes & SPELL_ATTR0_REQ_AMMO && (!IsAutoRepeatRangedSpell()) && !(AttributesEx9 & SPELL_ATTR9_AIMED_SHOT))
2523 castTime += 500;
2524
2525 return (castTime > 0) ? uint32(castTime) : 0;
2526}

2528uint32 SpellInfo::GetMaxTicks(uint32 difficulty) const
2529{
2530 int32 DotDuration = GetDuration();
2531 if (DotDuration == 0)
2532 return 1;
2533
2534 // 200% limit
2535 if (DotDuration > 30000)
2536 DotDuration = 30000;
2537
2538 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffectsForDifficulty(difficulty))
2539 {
2540 if (effect && effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
2541 switch (effect->ApplyAuraName)
2542 {
2543 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
2544 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL:
2545 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
2546 if (effect->ApplyAuraPeriod != 0)
2547 return DotDuration / effect->ApplyAuraPeriod;
2548 break;
2549 }
2550 }
2551
2552 return 6;
2553}

2559
2560std::vector<SpellInfo::CostData> SpellInfo::CalcPowerCost(Unit const* caster, SpellSchoolMask schoolMask) const
2561{
2562 std::vector<CostData> costs;
2563 auto collector = [this, caster, schoolMask, &costs](std::vector<SpellPowerEntry const*> const& powers)
2564 {
2565 costs.reserve(powers.size());
2566 int32 healthCost = 0;
2567
2568
2569 for (SpellPowerEntry const* power : powers)
2570 {
2571 if (power->RequiredAura && !caster->HasAura(power->RequiredAura))
2572 continue;
2573
2574 // Spell drain all exist power on cast (Only paladin lay of Hands)
2575 if (AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_DRAIN_ALL_POWER)
2576 {
2577 // If power type - health drain all
2578 if (power->PowerType == POWER_HEALTH)
2579 {
2580 healthCost = caster->GetHealth();
2581 continue;
2582 }
2583 // Else drain all power
2584 if (power->PowerType < MAX_POWERS)
2585 {
2586 CostData cost;
2587 cost.Power = Powers(power->PowerType);
2588 cost.Amount = caster->GetPower(cost.Power);
2589 costs.push_back(cost);
2590 continue;
2591 }
2592
2593 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "SpellInfo::CalcPowerCost: Unknown power type '%d' in spell %d", power->PowerType, Id);
2594 continue;
2595 }
2596
2597 // Base powerCost
2598 int32 powerCost = power->ManaCost;
2599 // PCT cost from total amount
2600 if (power->ManaCostPercentage)
2601 {
2602 switch (power->PowerType)
2603 {
2604 // health as power used
2605 case POWER_HEALTH:
2606 powerCost += int32(CalculatePct(caster->GetMaxHealth(), power->ManaCostPercentage));
2607 break;
2608 case POWER_MANA:
2609 powerCost += int32(CalculatePct(caster->GetCreateMana(), power->ManaCostPercentage));
2610 break;
2611 case POWER_RAGE:
2612 case POWER_FOCUS:
2613 case POWER_ENERGY:
2614 powerCost += int32(CalculatePct(caster->GetMaxPower(Powers(power->PowerType)), power->ManaCostPercentage));
2615 break;
2616 case POWER_RUNES:
2617 case POWER_RUNIC_POWER:
2618 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "CalculateManaCost: Not implemented yet!");
2619 break;
2620 default:
2621 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "CalculateManaCost: Unknown power type '%d' in spell %d", power->PowerType, Id);
2622 continue;
2623 }
2624 }
2625
2626 if (power->HealthCostPercentage)
2627 healthCost += int32(CalculatePct(caster->GetMaxHealth(), power->HealthCostPercentage));
2628
2629 // Flat mod from caster auras by spell school and power type
2630 Unit::AuraEffectList const& auras = caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_COST_SCHOOL);
2631 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator i = auras.begin(); i != auras.end(); ++i)
2632 {
2633 if (!((*i)->GetMiscValue() & schoolMask))
2634 continue;
2635
2636 if (!((*i)->GetMiscValueB() & (1 << power->PowerType)))
2637 continue;
2638
2639 powerCost += (*i)->GetAmount();
2640 }
2641
2642 // Shiv - costs 20 + weaponSpeed*10 energy (apply only to non-triggered spell with energy cost)
2643 if (AttributesEx4 & SPELL_ATTR4_SPELL_VS_EXTEND_COST)
2644 {
2645 uint32 speed = 0;
2646 if (SpellShapeshiftFormEntry const* ss = sSpellShapeshiftFormStore.LookupEntry(caster->GetShapeshiftForm()))
2647 speed = ss->CombatRoundTime;
2648 else
2649 {
2650 WeaponAttackType slot = BASE_ATTACK;
2651 if (AttributesEx3 & SPELL_ATTR3_REQ_OFFHAND)
2652 slot = OFF_ATTACK;
2653
2654 speed = caster->GetAttackTime(slot);
2655 }
2656
2657 powerCost += speed / 100;
2658 }
2659
2660 // Apply cost mod by spell
2661 if (Player* modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
2662 {
2663 if (power->PowerIndex == 0)
2664 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(Id, SPELLMOD_COST, powerCost);
2665 else if (power->PowerIndex == 1)
2666 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(Id, SPELLMOD_SPELL_COST2, powerCost);
2667 }
2668
2669 if (!caster->IsControlledByPlayer() && G3D::fuzzyEq(power->ManaCostPercentage, 0.0f) && SpellLevel)
2670 {
2671 if (Attributes & SPELL_ATTR0_LEVEL_DAMAGE_CALCULATION)
2672 {
2673 GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* spellScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.EvaluateTable(SpellLevel - 1, 0);
2674 GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* casterScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.EvaluateTable(caster->getLevel() - 1, 0);
2675 if (spellScaler && casterScaler)
2676 powerCost *= casterScaler->ratio / spellScaler->ratio;
2677 }
2678 }
2679
2680 // PCT mod from user auras by spell school and power type
2681 Unit::AuraEffectList const& aurasPct = caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_COST_SCHOOL_PCT);
2682 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator i = aurasPct.begin(); i != aurasPct.end(); ++i)
2683 {
2684 if (!((*i)->GetMiscValue() & schoolMask))
2685 continue;
2686
2687 if (!((*i)->GetMiscValueB() & (1 << power->PowerType)))
2688 continue;
2689
2690 powerCost += CalculatePct(powerCost, (*i)->GetAmount());
2691 }
2692
2693 if (power->PowerType == POWER_HEALTH)
2694 {
2695 healthCost += powerCost;
2696 continue;
2697 }
2698
2699 bool found = false;
2700 for (CostData& cost : costs)
2701 {
2702 if (cost.Power == Powers(power->PowerType))
2703 {
2704 cost.Amount += powerCost;
2705 found = true;
2706 }
2707 }
2708
2709 if (!found)
2710 {
2711 CostData cost;
2712 cost.Power = Powers(power->PowerType);
2713 cost.Amount = powerCost;
2714 costs.push_back(cost);
2715 }
2716 }
2717
2718 if (healthCost > 0)
2719 {
2720 CostData cost;
2721 cost.Power = POWER_HEALTH;
2722 cost.Amount = healthCost;
2723 costs.push_back(cost);
2724 }
2725 };
2726
2727 if (!_hasPowerDifficultyData) // optimization - use static data for 99.5% cases (4753 of 4772 in build 6.1.0.19702)
2728 collector(PowerCosts);
2729 else
2730 collector(sDB2Manager.GetSpellPowers(Id, caster->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID()));
2731
2732 // POWER_RUNES is handled by SpellRuneCost.db2, and cost.Amount is always 0 (see Spell::TakeRunePower)
2733 costs.erase(std::remove_if(costs.begin(), costs.end(), [](CostData const& cost) { return cost.Power != POWER_RUNES && cost.Amount <= 0; }), costs.end());
2734 return costs;
2735}

2774SpellInfo const* SpellInfo::GetAuraRankForLevel(uint8 level) const
2775{
2776 // ignore passive spells
2777 if (IsPassive())
2778 return this;
2779
2780 bool needRankSelection = false;
2781 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffectsForDifficulty(DIFFICULTY_NONE))
2782 {
2783 if (effect && IsPositiveEffect(effect->Effect) &&
2784 (effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA ||
2785 effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_PARTY ||
2786 effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_RAID) &&
2787 !effect->Scaling.Coefficient)
2788 {
2789 needRankSelection = true;
2790 break;
2791 }
2792 }
2793
2794 // not required
2795 if (!needRankSelection)
2796 return this;
2797
2798 for (SpellInfo const* nextSpellInfo = this; nextSpellInfo != NULL; nextSpellInfo = nextSpellInfo->GetPrevRankSpell())
2799 {
2800 // if found appropriate level
2801 if (uint32(level + 10) >= nextSpellInfo->SpellLevel)
2802 return nextSpellInfo;
2803
2804 // one rank less then
2805 }
2806
2807 // not found
2808 return NULL;
2809}

2833uint32 SpellInfo::GetSpellXSpellVisualId(Difficulty difficulty) const
2834{
2835 DifficultyEntry const* difficultyEntry = sDifficultyStore.LookupEntry(difficulty);
2836 while (difficultyEntry)
2837 {
2838 auto itr = _visuals.find(difficulty);
2839 if (itr != _visuals.end())
2840 for (SpellXSpellVisualEntry const* visual : itr->second)
2841 if (!visual->PlayerConditionID)
2842 return visual->ID;
2843
2844 difficultyEntry = sDifficultyStore.LookupEntry(difficultyEntry->FallbackDifficultyID);
2845 }
2846
2847 auto itr = _visuals.find(DIFFICULTY_NONE);
2848 if (itr != _visuals.end())
2849 for (SpellXSpellVisualEntry const* visual : itr->second)
2850 if (!visual->PlayerConditionID)
2851 return visual->ID;
2852
2853 return 0;

2868
2869void SpellInfo::_InitializeExplicitTargetMask()
2870{
2871 bool srcSet = false;
2872 bool dstSet = false;
2873 uint32 targetMask = Targets;
2874 // prepare target mask using effect target entries
2875 for (SpellEffectInfoMap::const_iterator itr = _effects.begin(); itr != _effects.end(); ++itr)
2876 {
2877 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : itr->second)
2878 {
2879 if (!effect || !effect->IsEffect())
2880 continue;
2881
2882 targetMask |= effect->TargetA.GetExplicitTargetMask(srcSet, dstSet);
2883 targetMask |= effect->TargetB.GetExplicitTargetMask(srcSet, dstSet);
2884
2885 // add explicit target flags based on spell effects which have EFFECT_IMPLICIT_TARGET_EXPLICIT and no valid target provided
2886 if (effect->GetImplicitTargetType() != EFFECT_IMPLICIT_TARGET_EXPLICIT)
2887 continue;
2888
2889 // extend explicit target mask only if valid targets for effect could not be provided by target types
2890 uint32 effectTargetMask = effect->GetMissingTargetMask(srcSet, dstSet, targetMask);
2891
2892 // don't add explicit object/dest flags when spell has no max range
2893 if (GetMaxRange(true) == 0.0f && GetMaxRange(false) == 0.0f)
2894 effectTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION);
2895
2896 targetMask |= effectTargetMask;
2897 }
2898 }
2899
2900 ExplicitTargetMask = targetMask;
2901}
2902
2903bool SpellInfo::_IsPositiveEffect(uint32 effIndex, bool deep) const
2904{
2905 // not found a single positive spell with this attribute
2906 if (Attributes & SPELL_ATTR0_NEGATIVE_1)
2907 return false;
2908
2909 switch (SpellFamilyName)
2910 {
2911 case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
2912 switch (Id)
2913 {
2914 case 29214: // Wrath of the Plaguebringer
2915 case 34700: // Allergic Reaction
2916 case 54836: // Wrath of the Plaguebringer
2917 return false;
2918 case 30877: // Tag Murloc
2919 case 61716: // Rabbit Costume
2920 case 61734: // Noblegarden Bunny
2921 case 62344: // Fists of Stone
2922 case 61819: // Manabonked! (item)
2923 case 61834: // Manabonked! (minigob)
2924 case 73523: // Rigor Mortis
2925 return true;
2926 default:
2927 break;
2928 }
2929 break;
2930 case SPELLFAMILY_MAGE:
2931 // Ignite
2932 if (SpellIconID == 45)
2933 return true;
2934 break;
2935 case SPELLFAMILY_PRIEST:
2936 switch (Id)
2937 {
2938 case 64844: // Divine Hymn
2939 case 64904: // Hymn of Hope
2940 case 47585: // Dispersion
2941 return true;
2942 default:
2943 break;
2944 }
2945 break;
2946 case SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE:
2947 switch (Id)
2948 {
2949 // Envenom must be considered as a positive effect even though it deals damage
2950 case 32645: // Envenom
2951 return true;
2952 default:
2953 break;
2954 }
2955 break;
2956 default:
2957 break;
2958 }
2959
2960 switch (Mechanic)
2961 {
2962 case MECHANIC_IMMUNE_SHIELD:
2963 return true;
2964 default:
2965 break;
2966 }
2967
2968 // Special case: effects which determine positivity of whole spell
2969 for (SpellEffectInfoMap::const_iterator itr = _effects.begin(); itr != _effects.end(); ++itr)
2970 {
2971 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : itr->second)
2972 {
2973 if (effect && effect->IsAura() && effect->ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_STEALTH)
2974 return true;
2975 }
2976 }
2977
2978 for (SpellEffectInfoMap::const_iterator itr = _effects.begin(); itr != _effects.end(); ++itr)
2979 {
2980 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : itr->second)
2981 {
2982 if (!effect || effect->EffectIndex != effIndex)
2983 continue;
2984
2985 switch (effect->Effect)
2986 {
2987 case SPELL_EFFECT_DUMMY:
2988 // some explicitly required dummy effect sets
2989 switch (Id)
2990 {
2991 case 28441:
2992 return false; // AB Effect 000
2993 default:
2994 break;
2995 }
2996 break;
2997 // always positive effects (check before target checks that provided non-positive result in some case for positive effects)
2998 case SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL:
2999 case SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL:
3000 case SPELL_EFFECT_SKILL_STEP:
3001 case SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL_PCT:
3002 case SPELL_EFFECT_ENERGIZE_PCT:
3003 return true;
3004 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_ENEMY:
3005 return false;
3006
3007 // non-positive aura use
3008 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA:
3009 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_FRIEND:
3010 {
3011 switch (effect->ApplyAuraName)
3012 {
3013 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_DONE: // dependent from bas point sign (negative -> negative)
3014 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STAT:
3015 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SKILL:
3016 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SKILL_2:
3017 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DODGE_PERCENT:
3018 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_PCT:
3019 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_DONE:
3020 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_DONE:
3021 if (effect->CalcValue() < 0)
3022 return false;
3023 break;
3024 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_TAKEN: // dependent from bas point sign (positive -> negative)
3025 if (effect->CalcValue() > 0)
3026 return false;
3027 break;
3028 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CRIT_PCT:
3029 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SPELL_CRIT_CHANCE:
3030 if (effect->CalcValue() > 0)
3031 return true; // some expected positive spells have SPELL_ATTR1_NEGATIVE
3032 break;
3033 case SPELL_AURA_ADD_TARGET_TRIGGER:
3034 return true;
3035 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
3036 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
3037 if (!deep)
3038 {
3039 if (SpellInfo const* spellTriggeredProto = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(effect->TriggerSpell))
3040 {
3041 // negative targets of main spell return early
3042 for (SpellEffectInfoMap::const_iterator it = spellTriggeredProto->_effects.begin(); it != spellTriggeredProto->_effects.end(); ++it)
3043 {
3044 for (SpellEffectInfo const* eff : itr->second)
3045 {
3046 if (!eff || !eff->Effect)
3047 continue;
3048 // if non-positive trigger cast targeted to positive target this main cast is non-positive
3049 // this will place this spell auras as debuffs
3050 if (_IsPositiveTarget(eff->TargetA.GetTarget(), eff->TargetB.GetTarget()) && !spellTriggeredProto->_IsPositiveEffect(eff->EffectIndex, true))
3051 return false;
3052 }
3053 }
3054 }
3055 }
3056 case SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
3057 // many positive auras have negative triggered spells at damage for example and this not make it negative (it can be canceled for example)
3058 break;
3059 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STUN: //have positive and negative spells, we can't sort its correctly at this moment.
3060 {
3061 bool more = false;
3062 for (SpellEffectInfoMap::const_iterator i = _effects.begin(); i != _effects.end(); ++i)
3063 {
3064 for (SpellEffectInfo const* eff : i->second)
3065 {
3066 if (eff && eff->EffectIndex != 0)
3067 {
3068 more = true;
3069 break;
3070 }
3071 }
3072 }
3073 if (effIndex == 0 && !more)
3074 return false; // but all single stun aura spells is negative
3075 break;
3076 }
3077 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_PACIFY_SILENCE:
3078 if (Id == 24740) // Wisp Costume
3079 return true;
3080 return false;
3081 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_ROOT:
3082 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SILENCE:
3083 case SPELL_AURA_GHOST:
3084 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
3085 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STALKED:
3086 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE_PERCENT:
3087 case SPELL_AURA_PREVENT_RESURRECTION:
3088 return false;
3089 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE: // used in positive spells also.
3090 // part of negative spell if cast at self (prevent cancel)
3091 if (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER)
3092 return false;
3093 break;
3094 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DECREASE_SPEED: // used in positive spells also
3095 // part of positive spell if cast at self
3096 if (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_UNIT_CASTER)
3097 return false;
3098 // but not this if this first effect (didn't find better check)
3099 if (Attributes & SPELL_ATTR0_NEGATIVE_1 && effIndex == 0)
3100 return false;
3101 break;
3102 case SPELL_AURA_MECHANIC_IMMUNITY:
3103 {
3104 // non-positive immunities
3105 switch (effect->MiscValue)
3106 {
3107 case MECHANIC_BANDAGE:
3108 case MECHANIC_SHIELD:
3109 case MECHANIC_MOUNT:
3110 case MECHANIC_INVULNERABILITY:
3111 return false;
3112 default:
3113 break;
3114 }
3115 break;
3116 }
3117 case SPELL_AURA_ADD_FLAT_MODIFIER: // mods
3118 case SPELL_AURA_ADD_PCT_MODIFIER:
3119 {
3120 // non-positive mods
3121 switch (effect->MiscValue)
3122 {
3123 case SPELLMOD_COST: // dependent from bas point sign (negative -> positive)
3124 if (effect->CalcValue() > 0)
3125 {
3126 if (!deep)
3127 {
3128 bool negative = true;
3129 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
3130 {
3131 if (i != effIndex)
3132 if (_IsPositiveEffect(i, true))
3133 {
3134 negative = false;
3135 break;
3136 }
3137 }
3138 if (negative)
3139 return false;
3140 }
3141 }
3142 break;
3143 default:
3144 break;
3145 }
3146 break;
3147 }
3148 default:
3149 break;
3150 }
3151 break;
3152 }
3153 default:
3154 break;
3155 }
3156
3157 // non-positive targets
3158 if (!_IsPositiveTarget(effect->TargetA.GetTarget(), effect->TargetB.GetTarget()))
3159 return false;
3160
3161 // negative spell if triggered spell is negative
3162 if (!deep && !effect->ApplyAuraName && effect->TriggerSpell)
3163 {
3164 if (SpellInfo const* spellTriggeredProto = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(effect->TriggerSpell))
3165 if (!spellTriggeredProto->_IsPositiveSpell())
3166 return false;
3167 }
3168 }
3169 }
3170 // ok, positive
3171 return true;
3172}

3174bool SpellInfo::_IsPositiveSpell() const
3175{
3176 // spells with at least one negative effect are considered negative
3177 // some self-applied spells have negative effects but in self casting case negative check ignored.
3178 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
3179 if (!_IsPositiveEffect(i, true))
3180 return false;
3181 return true;
3182}

3281void SpellInfo::_UnloadImplicitTargetConditionLists()
3282{
3283 // find the same instances of ConditionList and delete them.
3284 for (uint32 d = 0; d < MAX_DIFFICULTY; ++d)
3285 {
3286 for (uint32 i = 0; i < _effects.size(); ++i)
3287 {
3288 if (SpellEffectInfo const* effect = GetEffect(d, i))
3289 {
3290 ConditionContainer* cur = effect->ImplicitTargetConditions;
3291 if (!cur)
3292 continue;
3293 for (uint8 j = i; j < _effects.size(); ++j)
3294 {
3295 if (SpellEffectInfo const* eff = GetEffect(d, j))
3296 {
3297 if (eff->ImplicitTargetConditions == cur)
3298 const_cast<SpellEffectInfo*>(eff)->ImplicitTargetConditions = NULL;
3299 }
3300 }
3301 delete cur;
3302 }
3303 }
3304 }
3305}

3307SpellEffectInfoVector SpellInfo::GetEffectsForDifficulty(uint32 difficulty) const
3308{
3309 SpellEffectInfoVector effList;
3310
3311 // DIFFICULTY_NONE effects are the default effects, always active if current difficulty's effects don't overwrite
3312 SpellEffectInfoMap::const_iterator itr = _effects.find(DIFFICULTY_NONE);
3313 if (itr != _effects.end())
3314 effList = itr->second;
3315
3316 // downscale difficulty if original was not found
3317 // DIFFICULTY_NONE is already in our list
3318 DifficultyEntry const* difficultyEntry = sDifficultyStore.LookupEntry(difficulty);
3319 while (difficultyEntry)
3320 {
3321 SpellEffectInfoMap::const_iterator effectItr = _effects.find(difficulty);
3322 if (effectItr != _effects.end())
3323 {
3324 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : effectItr->second)
3325 {
3326 // overwrite any existing effect from DIFFICULTY_NONE
3327 if (effect)
3328 {
3329 if (effect->EffectIndex >= effList.size())
3330 effList.resize(effect->EffectIndex + 1);
3331
3332 if (!effList[effect->EffectIndex])
3333 effList[effect->EffectIndex] = effect;
3334 }
3335 }
3336 }
3337
3338 difficultyEntry = sDifficultyStore.LookupEntry(difficultyEntry->FallbackDifficultyID);
3339 }
3340
3341 return effList;
3342}
3343
3344SpellEffectInfo const* SpellInfo::GetEffect(uint32 difficulty, uint32 index) const
3345{
3346 DifficultyEntry const* difficultyEntry = sDifficultyStore.LookupEntry(difficulty);
3347 while (difficultyEntry)
3348 {
3349 SpellEffectInfoMap::const_iterator itr = _effects.find(difficulty);
3350 if (itr != _effects.end())
3351 if (itr->second.size() > index && itr->second[index])
3352 return itr->second[index];
3353
3354 difficultyEntry = sDifficultyStore.LookupEntry(difficultyEntry->FallbackDifficultyID);
3355 }
3356
3357 SpellEffectInfoMap::const_iterator itr = _effects.find(DIFFICULTY_NONE);
3358 if (itr != _effects.end())
3359 if (itr->second.size() > index)
3360 return itr->second[index];
3361
3362 return nullptr;
3363}
